cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of surrogate modelling and evolutionary techniques to design wind turbines. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions the use of evolutionary algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of wind turbines as a system. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper discusses the physical instantiation of wind turbine prototypes using a 3D printer. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of computational methods to design wind turbines.
